Twitter followers

Emily Darling

December 25, 2016

Twitter followers analysis

This analysis looks at how academics accumulate Twitter followers, and types of followers, during their social media career. This dataset comprises the 126749 unique followers of 110 full-time academics.

Followers have been classified into several major types of followers using coded keywords and combinations of keywords. The accuracy of classification was checked by hand, and resulted in ~89% correct classification (~11% misclassification rate).

Preliminary plots

NUVI provided us with a reach of each follower (along with their bio). Here, for each academic Twitter handle, Ive summed their total reach across each academics followers. Not surprisingly, reach increases exponentially with the number of followers (note the log10 x-axis). Maybe we could do a GAM or breakpoint analysis to look if theres a threshold here for when your total reach starts to increase?

Next, Ive calculated the average reach for the followers classified to each group.

We can then look at how the number of followers predicts which groups you accumulate (if we consider # of followers as a space-for-time comparison).
